{
    "node_id": "time-matrix-12",
    "title": "Unfinished Time: Since and For",
    "description": "Talking about how long you have been doing something using since and for.",
    "display_order": 12,
    "prerequisites": ["time-matrix-11"],
    "lesson_content_markdown": "# Unfinished Time: Since and For\n\nWe use the **Present Perfect** with **since** and **for** to talk about actions that started in the past and are still happening now. This tells us about **duration** or the **starting point**.\n\n### 1. Duration: For\nUse **for** when you talk about a **length of time** (how many minutes, hours, days, or years).\n\n- **Formula**: for + duration\n- **Example**: I have lived in this dorm **for six months**.\n- **Example**: She has studied science **for two hours**.\n\n### 2. Starting Point: Since\nUse **since** when you talk about the **specific time** an action started.\n\n- **Formula**: since + specific time point\n- **Example**: I have lived in this dorm **since September**.\n- **Example**: They have been friends **since 2022**.\n\n### 3. How long...?\nWe use **How long...?** to ask about the time an action has continued up until now.\n\n- **Example**: **How long** have you been in this class?\n- **Answer**: I've been in this class **for 30 minutes**.\n\n---",
